-- Calpers Commodity Holdings Dropped 4.1% in February to $1.279B
-- B y   E l i z a b e t h   C a m p b e l l
-- 2013-04-15T14:12:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-15/calpers-commodity-holdings-dropped-4-1-in-february-to-1-279b.html
The California Public Employees’
Retirement System, the largest U.S. pension fund, reported the
value of its commodity holdings slipped 4.1 percent in February
from the previous month.  The fund held $1.279 billion in commodities as of Feb. 28,
the most-recent data available, or 0.5 percent of the total
assets listed at $254.997 billion, according to a monthly  report 
posted on the fund’s website before today’s investment committee
 meeting . That’s down from $1.334 billion on  Jan. 31 , or 0.5
percent of total assets of $254.887 billion.  The fund’s board is meeting today, tomorrow and April 17,
according to the Calpers  website .  To contact the reporter on this story:
